Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.48,0:10:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1576,1038.667)}First, stage A
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.01,0:10:31.65,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,254.666)}{\c&HF0F1BB&}First Half: Stage A
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.14,0:10:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This is like 4 person Mahjong with only 2 players
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.15,0:10:31.65,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(952,878.666)}{\c&HF0F1BB&}Two people play in the same way as 4 person Mahjong
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.08,0:10:33.58,Default - top,,0,0,0,,Chii
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.95,0:10:35.75,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(968,870.667)}{\c&HF0F1BB&}You ca declare Chii off the player opposite
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.58,0:10:36.25,Default - top,,0,0,0,,You can declare Chii off the other player
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.25,0:10:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It differs as follows
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.91,0:10:44.38,Default - red - small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(320,265.333)}West Team
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.91,0:10:44.38,Default - blue - small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1626.667,265.333)}East Team
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.93,0:10:39.93,Default - top,,0,0,0,,Whether your hand is open or closed...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.48,0:10:44.38,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(981.333,868)}{\c&HF0F1BB&}You must openly declare you are in Tenpai
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.93,0:10:42.91,Default - top,,0,0,0,,if you're in Tenpai you must openly declare it
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.91,0:10:44.68,Default - top,,0,0,0,,Tenpai
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.68,0:10:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If your hand is closed you may also declare Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.50,0:10:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.78,0:10:51.18,Default - red - small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(341.333,262.666)}West Team
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.78,0:10:51.18,Default - blue - small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1621.333,273.333)}East Team
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.50,0:10:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus ends stage A
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.31,0:10:58.68,Default - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(962.667,654.667)\c&H747C56&}Stage A
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.72,0:10:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,In this style of Mahjong
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.81,0:10:58.68,Default - red,,0,0,0,,{\frz15.23\fscx206\fscy236\pos(978.667,617.334)\c&H1607B5&}Complete
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.05,0:10:58.68,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(954.667,748)\c&HECF1C1&}When either declares Tenpai, that style of play ends
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.26,0:10:56.30,Default - top,,0,0,0,,at the point when either player declares Tenpai
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.30,0:10:58.72,Default - top,,0,0,0,,The method of play previously followed completely ends
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.72,0:11:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,consequently speed is of the greatest advantage
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.05,0:11:06.45,Default - red - small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(325.334,268.001)}West Team
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.05,0:11:06.45,Default - blue - small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1616.001,273.334)}East Team
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.08,0:11:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The 2nd part is Stage B
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.31,0:11:06.45,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\c&HEDF6B5&\pos(954.667,678.667)}2nd Half: Stage B
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.54,0:11:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The side who hasn't declared Tenpai
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.51,0:11:12.98,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(976,868)\c&HF4F2BF&}Guesses opponents winning tile, presents 2 designated tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.54,0:11:09.26,Default - top,,0,0,0,,Guesses his opponent's winning tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.26,0:11:11.44,Default - top,,0,0,0,,Two designated tiles are presented
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.98,0:11:20.71,Default - red - small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(336,273.333)}West Team
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.98,0:11:20.71,Default - blue - small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1618.667,273.333)}East Team
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.98,0:11:20.71,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(402.667,644)}{\c&HF4F2BF&}Desginated Tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.98,0:11:20.71,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1536,649.333)}{\c&HF4F2BF&}Winning Tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.99,0:11:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,if there's a winning tile among the two
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.08,0:11:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the hand ends in a draw
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.98,0:11:20.71,Default - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(933.333,406.666)}Draw
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.47,0:11:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the side attempting to win...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.83,0:11:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,must without exceptions show their hand
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.83,0:11:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,this is to protect against false Tenpai declarations
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.95,0:11:32.61,Default - red - small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(336,273.333)}West Team
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.95,0:11:32.61,Default - blue - small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1618.667,273.333)}East Team
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.95,0:11:32.61,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(402.667,644)}{\c&HF4F2BF&}Desginated Tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.95,0:11:32.61,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1536,649.333)}{\c&HF4F2BF&}Winning Tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.98,0:11:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If there aren't any winning tiles among the two
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.68,0:11:32.61,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(968,51.999)\c&HE7E7C7&}{\c&HF4F2BF&}If among the designated tiles there are no winning tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.52,0:11:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the side declaring tenpai has the right to 5 draws
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.68,0:11:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(986.667,371.999)\c&H3DFBBD&}Gets the right to make 5 draws
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.97,0:11:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsumo!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.69,0:11:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,If they haven't completed their hands in 5 draws
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.71,0:11:42.05,Default - red - small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(336,273.333)}West Team
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.71,0:11:42.05,Default - blue - small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1618.667,273.333)}East Team
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.71,0:11:42.05,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(402.667,644)}{\c&HF4F2BF&}Desginated Tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.71,0:11:42.05,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1536,649.333)}{\c&HF4F2BF&}Winning Tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.71,0:11:42.05,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(632,401.332)}{\c&HF4F2BF&}Draws
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.55,0:11:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1008,94.666)\c&H29FBB1&}5 failed draws
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.73,0:11:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the stage goes back to the start
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.73,0:11:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Two tiles are selected to complete the Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.24,0:11:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,A successful reading of the hand ends the hand
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.28,0:11:56.08,Default - red - small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(336,273.333)}West Team
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.28,0:11:56.08,Default - blue - small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1618.667,273.333)}East Team
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.28,0:11:56.08,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(402.667,644)}{\c&HF4F2BF&}Desginated Tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.28,0:11:56.08,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1536,649.333)}{\c&HF4F2BF&}Winning Tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.83,0:11:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and if they can't, the side in Tepai can draw 5 more tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.41,0:11:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And it repeats in this manner
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.41,0:11:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,this continues while there are still safe tiles remaining
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.31,0:11:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(978.667,654.667)\c&H14C59B&}Special Rule
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.38,0:11:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a single special rule
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.65,0:12:03.75,Default - red - small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(421.333,86.667)}High Score {\c&HF4F2BF&}case:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.65,0:12:03.75,Default - blue - small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(424,582.667)}Low Score {\c&HF4F2BF&}case:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.65,0:12:03.75,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1381.334,214.667)}{\c&HF4F2BF&}Riichi, Tsumo, Sansyoku
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.65,0:12:03.75,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1373.334,692)}{\c&HF4F2BF&}Riichi, Tsumo
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.92,0:12:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If, for example, you make SanSyoku with 2 Man
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.63,0:12:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the hand has wildly different valuations depending on winning tile
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.87,0:12:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,If you draw the lower scoring tile
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.87,0:12:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you can lay the tile upside down
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.11,0:12:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You can refuse the Tsumo
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.18,0:12:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsumo!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.78,0:12:14.71,Default - black,,0,0,0,,{\pos(978.667,369.333)}2 Person Mahjong Basic Rules
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.78,0:12:14.71,Default - red,,0,0,0,,{\pos(962.667,827.999)}fin
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.72,0:12:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Other rules follow in that manner
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.18,0:12:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.48,0:12:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a style of play addressing luck,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.44,0:12:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and thus
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.56,0:12:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,their respective power levels...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.00,0:12:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,this game is an instrument to judge them
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.00,0:12:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And the dealer?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.00,0:12:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's determined at the start by die roll
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.22,0:12:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And then in the next hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.22,0:12:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and even the hand after that...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.22,0:12:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the person who last won
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.91,0:12:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,will continue being dealer
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.01,0:12:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That is to say
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.40,0:12:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,if you can't get a win
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.85,0:12:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The dealership is not transferred
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.16,0:12:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,After that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.16,0:12:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi while in Furiten is not allowed
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.67,0:12:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just silly
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.04,0:12:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And declaring Kan?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.52,0:13:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The same as in normal Mahjong
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.36,0:13:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,be it in either Stage A or B
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.12,0:13:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it's okay as long as it doesn't change your wait
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.55,0:13:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.55,0:13:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.23,0:13:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In closing there's a very important thing to remember
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.88,0:13:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This contest is limited to 2 hours!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.96,0:13:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,When two hours have passed the round we're in is the last one
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.68,0:13:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,First off this clock...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.05,0:13:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,is set to ring after 100 minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.66,0:13:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That is,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.00,0:13:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the last bell will ring 20 minutes before the end of the match
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.42,0:13:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.92,0:13:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,even if you stop the bell by pressing the top of the clock
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.60,0:13:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,this clock will ring again after 10 minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.88,0:13:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So therefore...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.64,0:13:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,20 minutes before the end of the match...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.17,0:13:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,10 minutes before, and then...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.65,0:14:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the final bell
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.50,0:14:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Those three times
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.88,0:14:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,All you have to judge the passage of time
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.73,0:14:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,are those three bells
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.69,0:14:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.58,0:14:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Then let us begin
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.71,0:16:11.81,Default - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1154.667,860)}First Game
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.71,0:16:11.81,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1141.334,945.334)\c&H0019FF&}Dealer-->{\c&HFFFFFF&} Ten: 0
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.71,0:16:11.81,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1240,1020)}Harada: 0
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.01,0:16:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got it
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.39,0:16:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,One tile from Chanta Tenpai
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.49,0:16:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,If he discards the 4 or 6 Man
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.59,0:16:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He can Tenpai
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.68,0:16:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Tenpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.65,0:16:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,f-fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.81,0:16:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.35,0:16:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,From now on we enter Stage B
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.08,0:16:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Harada, right off, in order to become dealer
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.35,0:17:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a high probability he put his hand together with speed as apriority
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.64,0:17:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,consequently, I suspect he's on a double sided wait beside the tile he used to declare Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.52,0:17:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.48,0:18:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsumo!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.09,0:18:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Riizumo (Riichi + Tsumo) with one Dora
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.95,0:18:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,4,000 points
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.48,0:18:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,If he had kept the 7 Sou and discarded the 1 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.84,0:18:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd have had a 3 way wait for a Mentanpin (Riichi + Tanyao + Pinfu) with one Dora
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.28,0:18:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did he take a middle wait?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.68,0:18:32.38,Default - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1154.667,860)}2nd Game
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.68,0:18:32.38,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1210.667,953.334)} Ten: 0
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.68,0:18:32.38,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1064,1028)\c&H0019FF&}Dealer--> {\c&HFFFFFF&}Harada: {\c&H00FF00&}4000
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.10,0:18:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Tenpai
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.95,0:18:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got it
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.69,0:19:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And so quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.21,0:19:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.91,0:19:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But why a middle wait on a 7 Man?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.19,0:19:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,If he discarded the 8 Man he would have had a 4/7 Man double sided wait
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.80,0:19:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and it would be Pinfu as well
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.97,0:19:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hunh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.07,0:20:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsumo
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.81,0:20:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Rizumo, Tanyao is 4,000 points
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.56,0:20:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I see
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.07,0:20:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Bad waits have the advantage in this Two Player Mahjong
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.44,0:20:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Two sided or multi sided waits...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.28,0:20:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,are stopped dead by any one of their winning tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.81,0:20:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,They're consequently easy to read
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.99,0:20:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Single tile or middle waits, however...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.81,0:20:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to complete them with only single tile...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.08,0:20:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They're difficult to read
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.61,0:22:11.21,Default - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(736,862.667)}3rd Game
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.61,0:22:11.21,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(842.667,948.001)\c&H0019FF&}Dealer--> {\c&HFFFFFF&}Ten: {\c&H00FF00&}4000
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.61,0:22:11.21,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(930.667,1036)}Harada: 4000
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.46,0:22:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.68,0:22:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If he completes this huge hand
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.65,0:22:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The points situation will dramatically change
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.20,0:22:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It might even, perhaps...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.12,0:22:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,close the book on this long struggle
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.40,0:22:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.78,0:22:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever he gets, a 1, 4, or 7 Man, he's then got a Green or Red Dragon wait
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.21,0:23:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But even if that's the case, Harada could turn it around with one step
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.34,0:23:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the absolute best that could happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.45,0:23:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If he discards that 3 Pin
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.24,0:23:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,He's in Tenpai with a 1/7 Main wait
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.26,0:23:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,W-why didn't he declare Tenpai?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.01,0:23:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,My god
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.08,0:23:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,IS HE GOING FOR A DAISANGEN?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.11,0:23:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Harada will soon be in Tenpai
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.11,0:23:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't do this. Ten!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.31,0:23:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't time for a hand above this
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.08,0:23:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn. He's in Furiten?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.88,0:24:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.41,0:24:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What a fucking draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.12,0:24:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That Green Dragon is the last one including the Dora indicator
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.37,0:24:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,To draw it now!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.59,0:24:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And because he drew it now...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.03,0:24:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Next turn he'll draw single tile wait that can't be read
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.00,0:24:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Will he declare Riichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.88,0:24:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.69,0:25:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We did it
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.21,0:25:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,No Riichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.25,0:25:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.64,0:25:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,WTF
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.39,0:25:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Ohhhh...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.39,0:25:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Harada doesn't think Ten has a hidden Green Dragon triplet
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.70,0:25:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Letting Harada know he's going for a DaiSanGen...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.97,0:25:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Harada will choose a Green Dragon to complete it
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.72,0:25:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that will be his priority
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.09,0:25:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten's single tile wait is the worst possible
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.32,0:25:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Harada has already discarded one of them
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.05,0:25:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,so there's only one remaining
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.36,0:25:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,but he can't wait any more
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.74,0:25:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If he gives Harada just one more chance...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.24,0:25:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,he'll for sure declare Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.24,0:25:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no choice but to take the 5 Man single wait
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.81,0:25:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,T-TEN?!?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.65,0:25:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You're STILL waiting?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.65,0:25:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If Harada declares Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.20,0:25:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,all this will come to nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.90,0:26:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's his turn again!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.91,0:26:29.18,Default - top,,0,0,0,,Harada,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.18,0:26:32.19,Default - top,,0,0,0,,I've kept you waiting
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.15,0:26:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I declare Tenpai
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.75,0:27:26.27,Default - top,,0,0,0,,That's crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.27,0:27:27.50,Default - top,,0,0,0,,Why Man tiles?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.50,0:27:29.50,Default - top,,0,0,0,,How did he know it was Man tiles?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.50,0:27:31.50,Default - top,,0,0,0,,From Ten's discards...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.50,0:27:33.90,Default - top,,0,0,0,,it's difficult to imagine it could be Man tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.90,0:27:37.07,Default - top,,0,0,0,,Looks more like a by-the-book Sou Honisou that doesn't need Man tiles
